      "writtenOn": "2026-04-17T07:46:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe the point here is: *IF* we are getting all the files in the change from the base to the latest patch-set, are we actually missing anything?\n\nLet\u0027s imagine that we are at PS2 and the difference between base and PS2 is:\n- file1\n- file2\n\nBut between base and PS1, there was file3 added, and that was removed in PS2.\nThen the list between PS1 and PS2 includes:\n- file3\n\nThat could be the case you\u0027re referring to.\n\n*In that specific case*, we should flag that file3 has been auto-owner-approved, if file3 is fully owned by the change owner. However, this API returns the result of the auto-owner-approved files of the *change* and not between PS2 and PS3, therefore the information that file3 is auto-owner-approved isn\u0027t relevant and cannot be displayed on the UI anyway: where are you going to put the icon next to?\n\nBottom line is: I get your point, and you are right; however, the case you are referring to, even if it is possible, won\u0027t be relevant anyway for this API execution.\n\nDoes the above make sense?",
