      "writtenOn": "2026-04-17T13:22:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, that makes sense.\nThe case I am thinking about is this:\n\nPS1\n- file1 - owned\n- file2 - non-owned\n\nChange Owner (and also owner) votes +2\n\nP2:\n- file3 - owned\n\nauto-owners-approval kicks in (only owned files have been modified), and the vote is copied over.\n\nI believe we have to look *only* at the last patchset to understand that *only* file3 was added, that it was owned, and that _therefore_ the auto-approval logic kicked in.\n\nPlease look at test `shouldReturnFilesAutoApprovedWhenNextPatchSetAddsOnlyOwnedFile`",
